<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1598,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1598,1624]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Leafhoppers with anterior margin of crown varying from rounded to narrowly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1352,1431,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1672,1696]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,195,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[151,1436,169,1647]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Exogonia capixaba sp. nov., male holotype: (1) body, lateral view; (2) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (3) pygofer, lateral view (illustrated mounted on a temporary slide with glycerin); (4) subgenital plate, ventral view; (5) connective and style, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (7) paraphyses, lateral view; (8) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321356/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,183,1637,1663]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">59</figureCitation>
), crown with epicranial, temporal, and frontogenal sutures usually visible. Pronotum generally with width approximately equal to transocular width; lateral margins convergent anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1174,1676,1702]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1672,1696]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,195,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[151,1436,169,1647]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Exogonia capixaba sp. nov., male holotype: (1) body, lateral view; (2) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (3) pygofer, lateral view (illustrated mounted on a temporary slide with glycerin); (4) subgenital plate, ventral view; (5) connective and style, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (7) paraphyses, lateral view; (8) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321356/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); dorsopleural carinae complete and oblique; posterior pronotal margin concave medially. Male pygofer strongly produced posteriorly, apical margin convex, usually with pair of ventral processes on apical portion bearing numerous setae (
<figureCitation box="[231,312,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1672,1696]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,195,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[151,1436,169,1647]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Exogonia capixaba sp. nov., male holotype: (1) body, lateral view; (2) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (3) pygofer, lateral view (illustrated mounted on a temporary slide with glycerin); (4) subgenital plate, ventral view; (5) connective and style, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (7) paraphyses, lateral view; (8) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321356/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[327,359,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">11</figureCitation>
); subgenital plates triangular (
<figureCitation box="[744,821,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1672,1696]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,195,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[151,1436,169,1647]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Exogonia capixaba sp. nov., male holotype: (1) body, lateral view; (2) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (3) pygofer, lateral view (illustrated mounted on a temporary slide with glycerin); (4) subgenital plate, ventral view; (5) connective and style, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (7) paraphyses, lateral view; (8) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321356/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); stalk of connective with median keel (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1421,1792,1818]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–75" captionStartId="18.[151,271,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[254,1340,189,1852]" captionTargetId="figure-72@18.[244,1346,163,1869]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 66–75. Exogonia hyalinosparsa (Melichar, 1932): (66) body, lateral view; (67-69) crown, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (70-75) male genitalia: (70) pygofer, lateral view; (71) subgenital plate, ventral view; (72) connective and style, dorsal view; (73) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (74) paraphyses, lateral view; (75) paraphyses, dorsal view. Specimens from Paraná State." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321384/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
); aedeagus expanded apically (
